At present, the host cells mostly used to establish HSV-2 
 in vitro model are Vero, HeLa, and VK2/E6E7 et al. (
 Akhrameyeva et al., 2011; 
 Davis et al., 1978; 
 Yao and Rosenthal, 2011). Since the primary culture technology of human vaginal epithelial cells cannot meet the needs of 
 in vitro research, it is a better choice using VK2/E6E7 as host cells to study the mechanism of HSV-2 infection.
